</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="72FAAC86FFA1B253F43BFD49FEAFA7E0" pageId="26" pageNumber="229" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3A5FFF0DFFA1B253F43BFD49FEAFA7E0" blockId="26.[114,646,579,746]" pageId="26" pageNumber="229">
DIAGNOSIS. — 
<taxonomicName id="FDE0848EFFA1B253F55EFD4AFE72A794" authorityName="Lendenfeld" authorityYear="1891" box="[279,406,646,670]" class="Calcarea" family="Sycanthidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="26" pageNumber="229" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">Sycanthidae</taxonomicName>
with coalescent radial tubes whose distal parts are supported by tangential triactines that form a loose meshwork perforated by large inhalant cavities.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="72FAAC86FFA1B253F43BFCD8FE30A1F3" pageId="26" pageNumber="229" type="description">
<paragraph id="3A5FFF0DFFA1B253F43BFCD8FEE6A626" blockId="26.[114,647,788,1275]" box="[114,258,788,814]" pageId="26" pageNumber="229">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A5FFF0DFFA1B253F43BFCFEFE30A1F3" blockId="26.[114,647,788,1275]" pageId="26" pageNumber="229">
We use the genus 
<taxonomicName id="FDE0848EFFA1B253F501FCFFFE32A646" authorityName="Jenkin" authorityYear="1908" box="[328,470,819,844]" class="Calcarea" family="Sycanthidae" genus="Dermatreton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="26" pageNumber="229" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0894231FFFA1B253F501FCFFFE32A646" box="[328,470,819,844]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="229">Dermatreton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the manner proposed by Jenkin (1908a). The loose cortex, which covers the distal parts of fused radial tubes, is in the form of a meshwork with broad openings formed by the inhalant spaces. As such it cannot give sufficient mechanical rigidity to the sponge, and consequently the atrial skeleton is thickened and rigid. Jenkin (1908a) has not designated the 
<typeStatus id="E55B41AFFFA1B253F4BAFBE4FEC5A148" box="[243,289,1064,1090]" pageId="26" pageNumber="229">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus. Among the originally included species we designate 
<taxonomicName id="FDE0848EFFA1B253F660FB8BFF78A174" authorityName="Jenkin" authorityYear="1908" class="Calcarea" family="Sycanthidae" genus="Dermatreton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="26" pageNumber="229" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="hodgsoni">
<emphasis id="0894231FFFA1B253F660FB8BFF78A174" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="229">D. hodgsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus id="E55B41AFFFA1B253F4B8FBA9FEC5A175" box="[241,289,1125,1151]" pageId="26" pageNumber="229">type</typeStatus>
species. Similar morphology is observed in 
<taxonomicName id="FDE0848EFFA1B253F54AFB48FD62A197" baseAuthorityName="Jenkin" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[259,646,1156,1183]" class="Calcarea" family="Sycanthidae" genus="Dermatreton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="26" pageNumber="229" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="scotti" subGenus="Tenthrenodes">
<emphasis id="0894231FFFA1B253F54AFB48FE77A197" box="[259,403,1156,1181]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="229">Dermatreton</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="0894231FFFA1B253F5EEFB49FDDCA195" box="[423,568,1157,1183]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="229">Tenthrenodes</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="0894231FFFA1B253F604FB48FD62A197" box="[589,646,1156,1181]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="229">scotti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="A2DBE388FFA1B253F433FB6FFF35A1B7" box="[122,209,1187,1213]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="26.[678,689,926,943]" captionTargetBox="[681,1204,228,890]" captionTargetId="figure-517@26.[671,1213,216,901]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIG. 24. — Diagram of the Dermatreton type of sponge wall organization. Abbreviations: ch, choanoderm; ic, inhalant cavities; cx, cortex." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5392215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5392215/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="229">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). The description and illustrations of 
<taxonomicName id="FDE0848EFFA1B253F43BFB0DFE91A1D6" authorityName="Jenkin" authorityYear="1908" box="[114,373,1217,1244]" class="Calcarea" family="Sycanthidae" genus="Dermatreton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="26" pageNumber="229" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="chartaceum">
<emphasis id="0894231FFFA1B253F43BFB0DFE91A1D6" box="[114,373,1217,1244]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="229">Dermatreton chartaceum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
suggest that it should be included in the genus 
<emphasis id="0894231FFFA1B253F528FB13FE30A1F3" box="[353,468,1247,1273]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="229">
<taxonomicName id="FDE0848EFFA1B253F528FB13FE34A1F3" authorityName="Borojevic &amp; Boury-Esnault &amp; Vacelet" authorityYear="2000" box="[353,464,1247,1273]" class="Calcarea" family="Jenkinidae" genus="Breitfussia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="26" pageNumber="229" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">Breitfussia</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
